 "logTail": [
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Ask him.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Sōan"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Name, age, where from. In that order.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "Three answers, and you do not have one of them. The silence goes on long enough that the physician looks up.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"What name did I give? When they pulled me out.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "You"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"None. You gave none. Three days I have had nothing to call you, and neither have you.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Sōan"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "Nothing comes.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "Genemon does not look surprised. He looks down and writes, and reads it back as he writes, aloud and once.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "One man, name unknown. Taken at the weir. Fed, three days. Condition, poor; hands, good.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"When he can stand, he rakes. The kitchen wants water before it wants anything.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "He goes. Sōan opens his ledger again, where his thumb kept the place.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"The days. I'll count from this one.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "You"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Day four, by mine. Yours can start where you like. Mark the post — notches hold.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Sōan"
  },
  {
   "channel": "milestone",
   "text": "Perk unlocked — The Notched Post: a day cut where fever cannot blur it. (+1 INT / −1 AGI)",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "On your feet, then. I am Genemon, steward of this house, and I keep the little it has left to keep. You'll not remember any of it, so hear it plain: the Kurosawa are samurai still — on the lord's rolls, if nowhere in the granary.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "(You say nothing, and reach for the spilled rice.)",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Nameless"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"...A man who works before he talks. Rare. We'll get on.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "milestone",
   "text": "Perk unlocked — Hands Before Words: A steady quickness that answers with work — trusting to no luck. (+1 SPD / −1 LUCK)",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "reward",
   "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "So you put your hands to it. Rake what grain is still whole back toward the basket, a fistful at a time. We reckon a samurai house’s worth in koku — a year’s eating for one man — and every basket you save us is a measure we need not go begging to the lord to make good.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "You can stop now, when the day is done — set the work down, and let the body take back what it can.",
   "count": 1
  }
 ],
